As a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ professional with 30 years of experience, Scott&#8217;s primary role at The USAA Educational Foundation is to help make the complicated world of personal finance easier for the military community to understand.
Scott also holds the professional designations of Chartered Financial Consultant, Certified Life Underwriter, Certified Project Manager, and Certified Diversity Professional (NDCCDP).
He is a native of Western Pennsylvania and earned a bachelor&#8217;s degree in accounting from Penn State University. Outside of his professional life, Scott enjoys spending as much time as possible with his wife and two sons.​​

